          "title": "About Metro Sports League",
          "path": "/about",
          "body": {
            "processed": "<p>Founded in 2010, the Metro Sports League has grown from a small local competition to the premier amateur sports league in the metropolitan area. With 24 teams across four divisions, we provide competitive opportunities for athletes of all skill levels.</p><h2>Our Mission</h2><p>To promote sportsmanship, community engagement, and athletic excellence through organized competitive sports. We believe in the power of sports to bring people together and inspire the next generation of athletes.</p><h2>League Structure</h2><ul><li><strong>East Division</strong> - 6 teams</li><li><strong>West Division</strong> - 6 teams</li><li><strong>North Division</strong> - 6 teams</li><li><strong>South Division</strong> - 6 teams</li></ul><h2>Season Format</h2><p>Each team plays 24 regular season games, followed by a single-elimination playoff tournament featuring the top 8 teams. The championship final is held at Metro Arena in June.</p>",
            "summary": "Founded in 2010, the Metro Sports League has grown from a small local competition to the premier amateur sports league in the metropolitan area. With 24 teams across four divisions, we provide competi"
          }
        }
      }
    }
